	<div class="row p-4 p-sm-5">
		<div class="col-md-6 order-md-2">
			<div class="traits">
				<h2>Watering Advice:</h2>
				<p class="descriptions">
					There are a few indicators to determine when to water a philodendron. Firstly, you can lift up the pot and if it is noticeably lighter than usual, the plant might need watering. You can also look at the top of the soil to see if it looks dry.
				</p>
				<p class="descriptions">
					The best method though is to push your finger about one or two inches into the soil. If the soil feels slightly damp, almost dry to the touch, then the plant needs watering. The soil should never be allowed to become either completely dry or soggy!
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
