		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="row p-4 p-sm-5">
		<div class="col-md-6">
			<div class="traits">
				<h2>General Guidelines:</h2>
				<ul class="fact-list">
					<li>
						Wipe the leaves with a damp cloth when they become dusty to improve leaf transpiration rate and appearance.
					</li>
					<li>
						Plants suffer when exposed to too cool or hot of conditions; keep away from cold drafts, heaters, and direct sunlight. 
					</li>
					<li>
						Low humidity or overfeeding can cause brown leaf tips; if low humidity is an issue, try placing a small dish of water near the plant to raise the humidity; a humidifier is also an option in overly dry environments.
					</li>
					<li>
						Too bright of light or overwatering can cause yellowing of leaves; refer to each plant on this site for preferred light levels.
					</li>
					<li>
						Philodendrons and monstera are poisonous and should not be ingested.
					</li>
					<li>
						Feed only during the spring and summer using a low strength, diluted, liquid plant food.
					</li>
					<li>
						Only purchase plants with plenty of foliage and without tears, spots, and leaf drop.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
